Boy, would I love to know the history of this old timer! It’s 115 years old and was made in the very last years of the old west. It’s definitely seen some action since pretty much of the finish has turned to a pleasing smooth plum brown color. But you get a very good solid C-O-L-T four clicks when you cock the hammer and the lock-up is like a bank vault door – not a speck of wiggle! The wood grips are a later replacement. All lettering is sharp and deep. The .32 WCF was a very popular caliber for the Single Action Army because it was interchangeable with the Winchester Model 1892 in that caliber being made at that time.
